views.text: Brazil's National Institute for Space Research announces that it has detected more than 39,000 wildfires in the Amazon rainforest since January.
At least 80 people are killed and 160 others injured in a bombing at a wedding in Kabul, Afghanistan.
The Treaty of Córdoba was signed, ratifying the Plan of Iguala and concluding Mexico's War of Independence from Spain.
